  "prompt": "What marks and rank is required to get Aerospace Engineering in IIT Bombay in JEE Advanced 2017?",
  "response": "In the JEE Advanced 2017, the closing rank for admission into the Aerospace Engineering program at IIT Bombay was around 87 for the general category. This means that candidates needed to achieve a rank close to this in order to be considered for admission. The exact marks required could vary each year based on the difficulty of the exam and the competition.\n\nFor reference, in JEE Advanced 2017, the overall marks required to secure such a rank would generally be in the range of 200-230, but these numbers can vary significantly each year. For the most accurate information regarding specific years, it is ideal to check the official IIT Bombay or JEE Advanced announcements or reports from that particular year.",
